ver Divine or anti-Divine in aim, is given a c=\r\nhance to run its course and actualize itself in the Universe. THAT is Her D=\r\nivine Compassion! That is why She is THE GREATEST Mother. She is mother to =\r\nthe Great Gods as much to the Danavas and Daityas, and Rakshasas and Bhutas=\r\n and Pretas and other corrupt human being and what not. \n&gt; \n&gt; Now coming to=\r\n your question on the phrase &quot;higher deities having less ability&quot;. I think =\r\nI have not been able to explain clearly, since in the last mail I was merel=\r\ny writing in the context of that discussion. Let me try here.\n&gt; \n&gt; There ar=\r\ne three basic layer of this Universe. The physical, the astral or subtle la=\r\nyer, and the causal (karana jagat) layer. In this subtle layer, which lies =\r\nsuperimposed on our own physical plane, there is a whole wide world of all =\r\npossible forces, just like in our own world. It is a layer which is created=\r\n out of force of pranashakti. This force of pranashakti in humans beings is=\r\n what causes all emotive movements on the consciousness - joy, happiness, l=\r\nove, passion, rage, fear, anger, hatred, disgust, lust, attachments etc etc=\r\n. These are also capable of influencing the thinking mind is us. Now the co=\r\nre philosophy of sadhana and specially Tantrik sadhana, is to create a form=\r\nation of the deity using ones own prana-shakti through the aid of repeated =\r\nrituals and procedures and mantras etc. If you think carefully, you will re=\r\nalize that every idol, ever homa agni needs a pranapratisthapana ritual bef=\r\nore starting. The sadhaka used the force of his/her own\n&gt;  pranashakti to i=\r\nnfuse life into a subtle formation of the deity. Once this process is succe=\r\nssfully done, this sublte formation of the deity which exists in the subtle=\r\n plane, has a life of its own. It can then guide the sadhaka through the pa=\r\nth and eventually, one day lead him/her to the real abode of the deity whic=\r\nh is the karana-jagat (beyond this astral plane). If a person is able to aw=\r\naken his/her Kundalini shakti, and make it identify/create such an astral f=\r\normation of the deity, it becomes an even more powerful force. It is, from =\r\nour limited human perspective, as much a powerful entity as we may imagine,=\r\n yet it is often not the actual Deity yet. Exactly the same thing has been =\r\ndescribed by Sri Vimalananda in the Aghora books, if you read carefully.=C3=\r\n=82=C2=A0 \n&gt; \n&gt; When a sadhaka has been able to associate with such an astr=\r\nal formation of the deity, it can guide the sadhaka along the path provided=\r\n the sadhaka also is trying to work hard and sincerely to reach the causal =\r\nplanes (the real spiritual planes of existence where the real force of the =\r\nDeity originates). The difference, if you ask, between this astral formatio=\r\nn of the deity and the real deity is that, the former is neither bound nor =\r\ncapable by itself of causing a complete and total transformation of the ave=\r\nrage human nature without a proactive help of the sadhaka. Whereas, if one =\r\nreaches the plane of the Great Gods, which is where the real deity exists, =\r\none cannot avoid being transformed in mind, emotions, body etc. And what ki=\r\nnd of a transformation will it be? One that will reflect to the world as a =\r\ngreater and genuine humility, sense of deep surrender to the Divine at ALL =\r\ntime and unfailingly, a complete withdrawal of lower nature of man - lust, =\r\nanger,\n&gt;  jealousy, greed, covetousness - an abiding peace, calm, detachmen=\r\nt, mental-illumination, genuine compassion, a widening of the consciousness=\r\n. Such an individual, even if he/she just sits down next to another person,=\r\n will exude a silent strong peace and unselfish love which will automatical=\r\nly calm the minds and disturbed emotions of lesser mortals ETC. THAT is the=\r\n authentic, unhindered flow of the Divine Power of any of the great deities=\r\n. This comes even if one deity is properly realized in the causal planes of=\r\n existence. But the astral formation of the same deity, which is created by=\r\n the force of our own pranashakti or Kundalini as the case maybe, is often =\r\nnot capable of affecting this kind of a total transformation in a sadhaka. =\r\nThat is why it is limited. It is not limited because it can&#39;t=C3=82=C2=A0 g=\r\net me a better job or a nice pay hike or cure some diseases or bring me fam=\r\ne or any such material benefit if I so ask of it - the astral formations of=\r\n the\n deities\n&gt;  can very easily do all these things in the physical world =\r\n- but it is limited because it cannot by itself give you the must authentic=\r\n and persistent spirituality of the higher planes, the one aim and destinat=\r\nion of all genuine sadhana.\n&gt; \n&gt; Since this astral plane is the way it is, =\r\ntherefore it&#39;s extremely important to keep actively working on ourselves to=\r\n increase detachment, objectivity, genuine internal surrender (when that ha=\r\nppens one accepts all life-situations without the slightest grudge), humili=\r\nty, control of anger, lust, jealousy etc. (all that is universally accepted=\r\n as spiritual qualities). For unless these changes are affected at least to=\r\n some degree in the mind and emotions of the sadhaka, one is simply not rea=\r\ndy to reach the higher planes of God and benefit from them spiritually. Mor=\r\neover, at every stage of spiritual evolution there is a gap between experie=\r\nnce and realization. Only repeated experiences *may* lead to realization. O=\r\nne off experiences create a force no doubt, but in time it fritters away, o=\r\nr worst, gets distorted by the impurities and conditioning of the sadhaka.\n=\r\n&gt; \n&gt; &lt;&lt;I am sure this is not your \n&gt; theory. You have taken it from yogi Au=\r\nrobindo. Many times when certain \n&gt; person reach a stage in their spiritual=\r\n path, others think whatever this guy is uttering is=C3=82=C2=A0complete tr=\r\nuth, when in fact it is=C3=82=C2=A0far from truth. \n&gt; Once=C3=82=C2=A0I saw=\r\n in a article that Aurobindo said that Divine Lord who spoke \n&gt; Gita comple=\r\ntely forgot it after few minutes or so. I could not believe \n&gt; what I was r=\r\neading. Then my respect for this yogi went down the drain.&gt;&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt; You suret=\r\ny is incorrect. There were certain events which happened in the last one an=\r\nd half years which made me sit down and rethink my own understanding of spi=\r\nrituality. At about the same time I started worshiping a specific personali=\r\nty of the Divine Mother, and the more I meditated on Her, the more would th=\r\noughts pour into my mind that my understanding of spirituality is imperfect=\r\n and has serious flaws. I tried, using my own meditations to find out what =\r\nwas wrong or rather imperfectly understood, what needed rethinking. First q=\r\nuestion I asked myself was, what is the aim of spirituality? My mind could =\r\ngrasp some outlines of certain answers and processes and truths. But it was=\r\n still not exceptionally clear.\n&gt; \n&gt; I had first read Sri Aurobindo when I =\r\nwas in college. I could not go beyond the first two pages. They were bounce=\r\nrs going one mile over my head. Three years ago someone gave me a book of S=\r\nri Aurobindo. I could understand say 10 percent, and rest I rejected, partl=\r\ny due to ignorance and partly due to egoistic arrogance. Never opened any o=\r\nf his writing since then. This year, as my sadhana was going on and as I wa=\r\ns instinctively trying to correct the flaws in my understanding, one day wh=\r\nile meditating I had an inner thought in the form of an image, which told m=\r\ne that I should start reading Sri Aurobindo but in a very specific manner. =\r\nThe image was very clear in my inner-eye, and thoroughly pressing on my con=\r\nsciousness. I opened his book again, and read it in the prescribed manner a=\r\nnd this time it made a LOT of sense to me. What I was struggling to underst=\r\nand all this year, whose outline I could grasp yet not get a proper hang of=\r\n, I was able to understand\n&gt;  from his writings with much deeper clarity.=\r\n=C3=82=C2=A0 Many of my own experiences made more sense to me. Many sentenc=\r\nes of Aghora books too made amply sense in a new light. I read 40 - 45 % of=\r\n his writings. Then something in me told me to stop at a certain point of h=\r\nis writings, for digesting the rest of the 60 % I will have to first make m=\r\nore spiritual progress. Otherwise the rational mind will distort the inform=\r\nation. So I stopped. He whom I had rejected firmly 3 years ago, now came ba=\r\nck to sit on my consciousness like a blazing sun. \n&gt; \n&gt; The line that you m=\r\nention, is from one of the earlier writings of Sri Aurobindo on the histori=\r\ncal problem of the Mahabharta. In the Mahabharata, there is an incident whi=\r\nch comes later on, after the great war and when Yudhisthira was ruling the =\r\nkingdom happily, when Arjuna asks Sri Krishna to repeat the words he had sp=\r\noken at the beginning of the war (The Gita) once more since he has forgotte=\r\nn them, and Sri Krishna says, the time has passed away (it was a special ti=\r\nme when the Gita was spoken), he cannot repeat the &quot;exact words&quot; once again=\r\n. \n&gt; \n&gt; Sri Krishna was the main Guru of Aurobindo. Even Swami Vivekananda =\r\nwas one of his Gurus, for during the time when Sri Aurobindo was in jail, f=\r\nor 15 days Swami Vivekananda would appear before him daily and instruct him=\r\n on the various layers of the mind, which he was not aware of till then. Sw=\r\nami Vivekananda had already left his physical body by then. It was in the w=\r\nritings of Sri Aurobindo that he mentioned about the left and right hemisph=\r\nere of the brain and their difference in functionality, and their connectio=\r\nn to spirituality, about 30 years before medical science confirmed the same=\r\n. \n&gt; \n&gt; Right from getting out of jail, to settling in Pondicherry, to push=\r\ning his own spiritual experiences further into states of Sahaja (which he d=\r\nescribes in different terminology), etc etc, he was guided continuously by =\r\nthe Adesha of Sri Krishna. He would literally hear the voice of Krishna spe=\r\naking to him, instructing him to do this or do that. Krishna was his Guru, =\r\nthe Divine Mother beyond all manifestation, was his destination. Anyway, my=\r\n point is not to try and sell Sri Aurobindo&#39;s perspective of spirituality. =\r\nI have benefited from it, but not necessary that everyone else will also be=\r\nnefit. There are so many sadgurus who have come to India, each with their u=\r\nnique perspectives and ideas and philosophies. Each must individually try a=\r\nnd find whose ideas gel properly with our mental and emotional makeup, and =\r\nhelp us to progress on the path. \n&gt; \n&gt; Though I now have a very deep respec=\r\nt for Sri Aurobindo, I maintain a safe distance from both his critics and h=\r\nis blind-admirers. Both of them, in my opinion, have misunderstood the dept=\r\nh of his teachings. Both their love and their hatred is a function of their=\r\n own egos, like it was mine 3 years ago, and not based on any genuine under=\r\nstanding or appreciation. In spirituality, no Sadguru can be understood acc=\r\nurately or even slightly without sincere sadhana.\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; &lt;&lt;\n&gt; Disclaimer--=\r\n-- My thinking is \n&gt; very different due to Darshan and=C3=82=C2=A0Grace of =\r\nDivine Mother & Divine \n&gt; Lord. Nobody should feel unhappy If I do not agre=\r\ne or follow the \n&gt; leader.Thanks.&gt;&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt; I at-least will never feel unhappy=\r\n if you disagree. There are \n&gt; many saints, many philosophies, many paths, =\r\nnot everyone is bound to \n&gt; like every path.=C3=82=C2=A0 Disagreement is pe=\r\nrfectly ok. Because someone \n&gt; disagrees with me or those whom I agree with=\r\n, does not mean I like him \n&gt; any less. I try to keep my=C3=82=C2=A0 emotio=\r\nnal side (where respect, love, \n&gt; dislike, hatred, anger, passions exist) s=\r\neparate from my thinking mind. \n&gt; It is very much possible, through practic=\r\ne, for a man to disassociate \n&gt; his rational-mind from the emotional-mind. =\r\nSo have no fears that your \n&gt; disagreement is going to make me like you any=\r\n less or any more.\n&gt; \n&gt; The problem with the emotional part of our being is=\r\n that it jumps up at appearances, running ahead to grasp the truth rather t=\r\nhan waiting patiently for the truth to arrive in all its aspects and dimens=\r\nions, and in the process it distorts the truth and then reacts to that dist=\r\norted image. For example, recently in some social forums I posted a comment=\r\n that I found the Tantrik Adwaitha far more appealing than Sri Adi Shankara=\r\n&#39;s Adwaitha, though the Adwaitha of Adi Shankara has many hard-selling supp=\r\norters. Immediately some friends of mine on Twitter and otherwise, jumped t=\r\no the false conclusion that I have disrespected Adi Shankara, and tried bes=\r\nt to make me &quot;see the truth&quot; by such grandiose statements that=C3=82=C2=A0 =\r\nShankara is the &#39;final word&#39; on Adwaitha and everything else must be necess=\r\narily lesser. Or that I was making an egoistic denouncement. Both of which =\r\nare million light-years away from the truth. That Sri Adi Shankara was a sp=\r\necial Vibhuti\n&gt;  (manifestation) of God, that much I am certain. His compos=\r\nitions are so brilliant that it can&#39;t be sufficiently appreciated in words.=\r\n Yet, I have equally no qualms in rejecting his philosophy. And because I a=\r\nm not bound to accept his philosophy, does not mean I respect or love him a=\r\nny less than any other great saint.=C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt; \n&gt; If you disrespect a ma=\r\nn, and specially a saint, and then start disliking him too with a passion, =\r\nyou are creating strong negative karmas. But if you can disagree with someo=\r\nne without losing respect or love for the person, in an objective manner, y=\r\nou reap very little karmic effects. That is why Lord Krishna too advices us=\r\n to become more detached in life.\n&gt; \n&gt; In conclusion, Narasimha is totally =\r\ncorrect. Many things cannot be sufficiently expressed in words without caus=\r\ning some distortion.\n&gt; \n&gt; -Regards\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0Rajarshi\n&gt; \n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0=\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\n&gt; param bhAwamajAnant=\r\no mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; ________________________________\n&gt;  =\r\nFrom: Laxmi Narayan &lt;shrijishrihari@...&gt;\n&gt; To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@...=\r\nm&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt; Sent: Thursday, 11 October 2012 12:21 =\r\nAM\n&gt; Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: A thought\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0 \n&gt; \n&gt; \n=\r\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0 \n&gt; Dear Rajarshi Bhai,\n&gt; How are you doing? About 200 hundre=\r\nd years ago, a man made a theory of creation in France. When Napolean asked=\r\n where is God in it, the guy said, do not talk about God. It makes things c=\r\nomplicated.\n&gt; So is there a place for Divine Mother and Her Love or Grace o=\r\nr Protection in your theory. Is=C3=82=C2=A0this intermediate zone as you sa=\r\ny is created by Her and part of Her creation=C3=82=C2=A0or by=C3=82=C2=A0so=\r\nmebody else.=C3=82=C2=A0 Does=C3=82=C2=A0She needs some visa to go there if=\r\n she is=C3=82=C2=A0not the Creater.=C3=82=C2=A0As you say all higher deity =\r\nare there but less in ability. Does the deities have even less =C3=82=C2=A0=\r\nability on earth plane.\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt; I am sure this is not your theory.=\r\n You have taken it from yogi Aurobindo. Many times when certain person reac=\r\nh a stage in their spiritual path, others think whatever this guy is utteri=\r\nng is=C3=82=C