 manifest the &quot;antaratmah&quot; as an unfailing =\r\nguide to the path.\n&gt; \n&gt; In a nutshell, a genuine &quot;experience&quot; is good and a=\r\nuthentic only to the extent that it helps to modify and transform your waki=\r\nng surface personality. That is the only true test. Rest all the range of e=\r\nxperiences that come from this realm, and 95 percent of Yogis get experienc=\r\nes ONLY from this realm, are just sound and fury without substance. \n&gt; \n&gt; I=\r\nn the writings of Sri Aurobindo, he calls it the intermediate zone, which h=\r\nas destroyed innumerable yogis who have got swept away by the light and sou=\r\nnd of this realm. One sure-shot way to cross this realm, and all sadhakas w=\r\nill have to cross this some day, is to hang on tightly to the fundamentals.=\r\n\n&gt; \n&gt; -Regards\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0Rajarshi \n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; awaktam wyaktimApannam manya=\r\nntE mAmabuddhayah |\n&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n&gt; \n=\r\n&gt; From: vedic_pathak &lt;vedic_pathak@...&gt;\n&gt; To: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com =\r\n\n&gt; Sent: Tuesday, 9 October 2012 9:07 AM\n&gt; Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: A th=\r\nought\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0 \n&gt; Dear Rajarshi,\n&gt; \n&gt; A sage &quot;sms&quot; indeed! Yes =\r\ndirection must be always, always the top most priority. It reminded me of s=\r\nimple, yet quite effective day to day example of driving Car. One can not m=\r\niss/ignore the sight of correct road to the destination even for a split se=\r\ncond. However, Optimised &quot;controlled&quot; speed (even if very fast by set stand=\r\nards) could be an added advantage while not loosing the sight of the road.\n=\r\n&gt; \n&gt; Best Regards,\n&gt; \n&gt; Utpal \n&gt; \n&gt; --- In mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroup=\r\ns.com, &quot;rajarshi14&quot; &lt;rajarshi14@&gt; wrote:\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Got an sms from a good fri=\r\nend today. Thought I will share it here.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; &quot;Progress has little to d=\r\no with speed; but much to do with direction. So always concentrate on your =\r\ndirection, not on speed.&quot;\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; For any genuine spiritual seeker, this\n&gt;=\r\n  is one of the sanest advices, ever. In the milieu of spirituality, too ma=\r\nny people get caught up in the less important - aka, visions, &#39;experiences&#39;=\r\n, tough-penances, complex rituals, offbeat sadhanas etc etc, while forgetti=\r\nng the goal of real spirituality, that is transformation of mind/emotions/b=\r\nody resulting in greater surrender to the Divine, greater equanimity to lif=\r\ne situations, an abiding calm and peace, genuine humility, lessening of low=\r\ner emotions like lust, anger, jealously, hatred, cravings, furious attachme=\r\nnts, such that eventually every action of the individual is like a consecra=\r\ntion (sacrifice, yagjya) to the Divine. A life so transformed and so away f=\r\nrom our average superficial existence, that it becomes a fulfillment on its=\r\n own. God is not the finish line of a bicycle race. It is the progressive u=\r\nnfolding of a transformation process.\n&gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; Complex rituals and speedy s=\r\nadhanas and experiences et al are ok, provided one does not\n&gt;  lose sight o=\r\nf the fundamentals. THEN these can be useful. Otherwise one ends up running=\r\n in circles and going nowhere. An experience-chaser is not necessary a spir=\r\nitual entity. I had to learn this basic truth the hard-way.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt;\n\n\n \r\n---2020808392-473503936-1349990793=:27561\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;html&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:#000; background-color:#fff; font-family:ar=\r\nial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div=\r\n&gt;&nbsp;Dear Utpal,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;&lt;&lt;br&gt;\nIt may require a LOT to reject philo=\r\nsophy of giant such as adi Shankara and yet some one may not be able to rej=\r\nect afterall. &gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Philosophy is pure rational thought. Spiritua=\r\nlity on the other hand is experiential. One can sit in an armchair and cont=\r\nemplate on philosophy, but the same is not possible in case of spirituality=\r\n. These two are different. Philosophy gives a logical framework of understa=\r\nnding something. There could be philosophy of science, a philosophy of ethi=\r\ncs, a philosophy of spirituality, a philosophy of epistemology (the investi=\r\ngations into the process of acquiring knowledge) etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;That Sri Adi S=\r\nhankara was a fantastic spiritual giant, I have no doubt (which I have alre=\r\nady stated in my previous email. Vibhuti of God). I am also sure that the v=\r\nery presence of such a man of such spiritual stature would have naturally d=\r\nrawn masses towards him.&nbsp; It happens with all great personalities. The=\r\ny have a magnetism which extends\n way beyond after their death.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Howe=\r\nver, to understand, appreciate, criticize, debate, analyses, comparatively-=\r\nevaluate any philosophy of any individual is not that difficult and is a va=\r\nlid rational process. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;While future is always uncertain, but chances=\r\n look remote for me that I would find Mayavada more attractive. It was Sri =\r\nAdi Shankara&#39;s Mayavada - as is understood and propagated by his followers =\r\n- which I had studied when I was first trying to get a grasp of Hindu philo=\r\nsophy. It a nice, compact and easily understandable philosophy. Possibly on=\r\ne the chief reasons why most&nbsp; intellectuals like his Adwaitha apart fr=\r\nom being attracted by his personality. It is easier to debate from Sri Shan=\r\nkara&#39;s stand-point. At that time I liked it. Later as I got acquainted myse=\r\nlf with more varieties of Hindu philosophy, I found others more comprehensi=\r\nve and covering more essential points and using a very, if I may use this p=\r\nhrase, a bottom-up\n approach to understanding reality, while Sri Shankara&#39;s=\r\n philosophy is a very top-down approach, with a greater thrust on the top a=\r\nnd an indeterminate leftover in the bottom. Shankara&#39;s Adwaitha, Ramanujach=\r\narya&#39;s Visistha-adwaitha, Vallavacharya&#39;s Suddha Adwaitha - so many varieti=\r\nes of philosophy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I have a personal view about judging philosophy. F=\r\nor everything that one giant has said, there is always another one who has =\r\nsaid exactly the opposite. And a third and forth one who came up with a dif=\r\nferent view-point, differing with all the previous ones. And each of these =\r\ngiants have spoken with the utmost conviction of their own realizations of =\r\ntruths. So personality and stature of the philosopher should play no role i=\r\nn an objective analysis of the philosophy. Just like the personality and st=\r\nature of a mathematician is of no use in&nbsp; judging the correctness of a=\r\n mathematical theory.&nbsp; Spiritually, the reality is same (and it maybe =\r\na very\n complex reality). But philosophically each have differences which c=\r\nannot the ignored. In such an intellectual climate, in my personal opinion,=\r\n it is fair enough to discard one philosophy for another, after a thorough =\r\nand detailed contemplation of the pros and cons.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;From a spiritual vi=\r\new-point all this is utterly meaningless. Which ever spiritual giant one ch=\r\nooses to hang on to, if sincere faith, reverence and effort is engaged, sur=\r\nely progress will happen in time. But philosophy is a another matter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;[To make my stand clearer, let me say hypothetically that IF by some stra=\r\nnge miracle of God, Sri Adi Shankara were to come and stand infornt of me, =\r\nI would have no qualms about falling at his feet and bowing down to him and=\r\n asking for his blessings, for his spiritual stature is unquestionable. Yet=\r\n I will still not be agreeable to the philosophy he propagated during the t=\r\nime he lived.]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Best\n Regards&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;Apple-style-s=\r\npan&quot; style=3D&quot;font-size:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=3D=\r\n&quot;color:rgb(153, 153, 153);&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;yui_3_2_0_=\r\n2_134243527249950&quot; style=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times, s=\r\nerif;&quot;&gt;awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span c=\r\nlass=3D&quot;yui_3_2_0_2_134243506227946 yui_3_2_0_2_134243527249952 yui_3_2_0_6=\r\n1_134997453972586&quot; style=3D&quot;FONT-SIZE:10pt;COLOR:navy;FONT-FAMILY:Verdana;&quot;=\r\n&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt; param bhAwamaj=\r\nAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/b&gt;=\r\n&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, san=\r\ns-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family: times new roman, new=\r\n york, times, serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Ari=\r\nal&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span\n style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From=\r\n:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vedic_pathak &lt;vedic_pathak@...&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com &lt;br&gt; &lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Thursday, 11 October 2=\r\n0