p;this intermediate zone as you say is created by Her &lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n&gt; and part of Her creation=C3=82&nbsp;or by=C3=82&nbsp;somebody else. =\r\n&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; There is no other somebody else in the Universe=\r\n apart from Her. Even the worst Asura is also Her creation to sustain this =\r\nworld, for reasons only She knows, because Her perspective/vision is way be=\r\nyond even the sharpest human mind. Nobody, can understand mentally, all of =\r\nHer actions, for She is truly the One whose energy has created the Universe=\r\n of diversity, She lies hidden inside it as well as beyond it, awaiting pat=\r\niently to be discovered, extending Her love, truth, force and power to the =\r\naid of anyone who calls Her sincerely and unconditionally, yet allowing eve=\r\nry creature the liberty to act as per its own understanding, for causes app=\r\narently good or the apparently bad. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;&lt;Does=C3=82&=\r\nnbsp;She needs some visa &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; to go there if she is=C3=82&nbsp;not the=\r\n Creater.=C3=82&nbsp;As you say all higher deity are &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; there but le=\r\nss in ability. Does the deities have even less =C3=82&nbsp;ability on &lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; earth plane.&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; She needs no visa, but neither=\r\n does She interfere without a genuine cause or a genuine call. Everything i=\r\ns Her world, then why is there ugliness, crime, evil things? Who creates th=\r\ne Asuras, if not She? And it is She herself who gave them the liberty to ac=\r\nt as per their freewill. This world is a play of forces and a democracy of =\r\nopportunities. Every impulse, however Divine or anti-Divine in aim, is give=\r\nn a chance to run its course and actualize itself in the Universe. THAT is =\r\nHer Divine Compassion! That is why She is THE GREATEST Mother. She is mothe=\r\nr to the Great Gods as much to the Danavas and Daityas, and Rakshasas and B=\r\nhutas and Pretas and other corrupt human being and what not. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; Now coming to your question on the phrase &quot;higher deities having less=\r\n ability&quot;. I think I have not been able to explain clearly, since in the la=\r\nst mail I was merely writing in the context of that discussion. Let me try =\r\nhere.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; There are three basic layer of this Universe. The =\r\nphysical, the astral or subtle layer, and the causal (karana jagat) layer. =\r\nIn this subtle layer, which lies superimposed on our own physical plane, th=\r\nere is a whole wide world of all possible forces, just like in our own worl=\r\nd. It is a layer which is created out of force of pranashakti. This force o=\r\nf pranashakti in humans beings is what causes all emotive movements on the =\r\nconsciousness - joy, happiness, love, passion, rage, fear, anger, hatred, d=\r\nisgust, lust, attachments etc etc. These are also capable of influencing th=\r\ne thinking mind is us. Now the core philosophy of sadhana and specially Tan=\r\ntrik sadhana, is to create a formation of the deity using ones own prana-sh=\r\nakti through the aid of repeated rituals and procedures and mantras etc. If=\r\n you think carefully, you will realize that every idol, ever homa agni need=\r\ns a pranapratisthapana ritual before starting. The sadhaka used the force o=\r\nf his/her\n own&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  pranashakti to infuse life into a subtle formation=\r\n of the deity. Once this process is successfully done, this sublte formatio=\r\nn of the deity which exists in the subtle plane, has a life of its own. It =\r\ncan then guide the sadhaka through the path and eventually, one day lead hi=\r\nm/her to the real abode of the deity which is the karana-jagat (beyond this=\r\n astral plane). If a person is able to awaken his/her Kundalini shakti, and=\r\n make it identify/create such an astral formation of the deity, it becomes =\r\nan even more powerful force. It is, from our limited human perspective, as =\r\nmuch a powerful entity as we may imagine, yet it is often not the actual De=\r\nity yet. Exactly the same thing has been described by Sri Vimalananda in th=\r\ne Aghora books, if you read carefully.=C3=82&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; When=\r\n a sadhaka has been able to associate with such an astral formation of the =\r\ndeity, it can guide the sadhaka along the path provided the sadhaka also is=\r\n trying to work hard and sincerely to reach the causal planes (the real spi=\r\nritual planes of existence where the real force of the Deity originates). T=\r\nhe difference, if you ask, between this astral formation of the deity and t=\r\nhe real deity is that, the former is neither bound nor capable by itself of=\r\n causing a complete and total transformation of the average human nature wi=\r\nthout a proactive help of the sadhaka. Whereas, if one reaches the plane of=\r\n the Great Gods, which is where the real deity exists, one cannot avoid bei=\r\nng transformed in mind, emotions, body etc. And what kind of a transformati=\r\non will it be? One that will reflect to the world as a greater and genuine =\r\nhumility, sense of deep surrender to the Divine at ALL time and unfailingly=\r\n, a complete withdrawal of lower nature of man - lust,\n anger,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  je=\r\nalousy, greed, covetousness - an abiding peace, calm, detachment, mental-il=\r\nlumination, genuine compassion, a widening of the consciousness. Such an in=\r\ndividual, even if he/she just sits down next to another person, will exude =\r\na silent strong peace and unselfish love which will automatically calm the =\r\nminds and disturbed emotions of lesser mortals ETC. THAT is the authentic, =\r\nunhindered flow of the Divine Power of any of the great deities. This comes=\r\n even if one deity is properly realized in the causal planes of existence. =\r\nBut the astral formation of the same deity, which is created by the force o=\r\nf our own pranashakti or Kundalini as the case maybe, is often not capable =\r\nof affecting this kind of a total transformation in a sadhaka. That is why =\r\nit is limited. It is not limited because it can&#39;t=C3=82&nbsp; get me a bett=\r\ner job or a nice pay hike or cure some diseases or bring me fame or any suc=\r\nh material benefit if I so ask of it - the astral formations of\n the deitie=\r\ns&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  can very easily do all these things in the physical world - but=\r\n it is limited because it cannot by itself give you the must authentic and =\r\npersistent spirituality of the higher planes, the one aim and destination o=\r\nf all genuine sadhana.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Since this astral plane is the wa=\r\ny it is, therefore it&#39;s extremely important to keep actively working on our=\r\nselves to increase detachment, objectivity, genuine internal surrender (whe=\r\nn that happens one accepts all life-situations without the slightest grudge=\r\n), humility, control of anger, lust, jealousy etc. (all that is universally=\r\n accepted as spiritual qualities). For unless these changes are affected at=\r\n least to some degree in the mind and emotions of the sadhaka, one is simpl=\r\ny not ready to reach the higher planes of God and benefit from them spiritu=\r\nally. Moreover, at every stage of spiritual evolution there is a gap betwee=\r\nn experience and realization. Only repeated experiences *may* lead to reali=\r\nzation. One off experiences create a force no doubt, but in time it fritter=\r\ns away, or worst, gets distorted by the impurities and conditioning of the =\r\nsadhaka.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;&lt;I am sure this is not your &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; th=\r\neory. You have taken it from yogi Aurobindo. Many times when certain &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; person reach a stage in their spiritual path, others think whatever thi=\r\ns guy is uttering is=C3=82&nbsp;complete truth, when in fact it is=C3=82&nb=\r\nsp;far from truth. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Once=C3=82&nbsp;I saw in a article that Aurobi=\r\nndo said that Divine Lord who spoke &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Gita completely forgot it aft=\r\ner few minutes or so. I could not believe &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; what I was reading. The=\r\nn my respect for this yogi went down the drain.&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nYou surety is incorrect. There were certain events which happened in the la=\r\nst one and half years which made me sit down and rethink my own understandi=\r\nng of spirituality. At about the same time I started worshiping a specific =\r\npersonality of the Divine Mother, and the more I meditated on Her, the more=\r\n would thoughts pour into my mind that my understanding of spirituality is =\r\nimperfect and has serious flaws. I tried, using my own meditations to find =\r\nout what was wrong or rather imperfectly understood, what needed rethinking=\r\n. First question I asked myself was, what is the aim of spirituality? My mi=\r\nnd could grasp some outlines of certain answers and processes and truths. B=\r\nut it was still not exceptionally clear.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; I had first rea=\r\nd Sri Aurobindo when I was in college. I could not go beyond the first two =\r\npages. They were bouncers going one mile over my head. Three years ago some=\r\none gave me a book of Sri Aurobindo. I could understand say 10 percent, and=\r\n rest I rejected, partly due to ignorance and partly due to egoistic arroga=\r\nnce. Never opened any of his writing since then. This year, as my sadhana w=\r\nas going on and as I was instinctively trying to correct the flaws in my un=\r\nderstanding, one day while meditating I had an inner thought in the form of=\r\n an image, which told me that I should start reading Sri Aurobindo but in a=\r\n very specific manner. The image was very clear in my inner-eye, and thorou=\r\nghly pressing on my consciousness. I opened his book again, and read it in =\r\nthe prescribed manner and this time it made a LOT of sense to me. What I wa=\r\ns struggling to understand all this year, whose outline I could grasp yet n=\r\not get a proper hang of, I was able to\n understand&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  from his writi=\r\nngs with much deeper clarity.=C3=82&nbsp; Many of my own experiences made m=\r\nore sense to me. Many sentences of Aghora books too made amply sense in a n=\r\new light. I read 40 - 45 % of his writings. Then something in me told me to=\r\n stop at a certain point of his writings, for digesting the rest of the 60 =\r\n% I will have to first make more spiritual progress. Otherwise the rational=\r\n mind will distort the information. So I stopped. He whom I had rejected fi=\r\nrmly 3 years ago, now came back to sit on my consciousness like a blazing s=\r\nun. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; The line that you mention, is from one of the earli=\r\ner writings of Sri Aurobindo on the historical problem of the Mahabharta. I=\r\nn the Mahabharata, there is an incident which comes later on, after the gre=\r\nat war and when Yudhisthira was ruling the kingdom happily, when Arjuna ask=\r\ns Sri Krishna to repeat the words he had spoken at the beginning of the war=\r\n (The Gita) once more since he has forgotten them, and Sri Krishna says, th=\r\ne time has passed away (it was a special time when the Gita was spoken), he=\r\n cannot repeat the &quot;exact words&quot; once again. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Sri Krishn=\r\na was the main Guru of Aurobindo. Even Swami Vivekananda was one of his Gur=\r\nus, for during the time when Sri Aurobindo was in jail, for 15 days Swami V=\r\nivekananda would appear before him daily and instruct him on the various la=\r\nyers of the mind, which he was not aware of till then. Swami Vivekananda ha=\r\nd already left his physical body by then. It was in the writings of Sri Aur=\r\nobindo that he mentioned about the left and right hemisphere of the brain a=\r\nnd their difference in functionality, and their connection to spirituality,=\r\n about 30 years before medical science confirmed the same. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; Right from getting out of jail, to settling in Pondicherry, to pushing =\r\nhis own spiritual experiences further into states of Sahaja (which he descr=\r\nibes in different terminology), etc etc, he was guided continuously by the =\r\nAdesha of Sri Krishna. He would literally hear the voice of Krishna speakin=\r\ng to him, instructing him to do this or do that. Krishna was his Guru, the =\r\nDivine Mother beyond all manifestation, was his destination. Anyway, my poi=\r\nnt is not to try and sell Sri Aurobindo&#39;s perspective of spirituality. I ha=\r\nve benefited from it, but not necessary that everyone else will also benefi=\r\nt. There are so many sadgurus who have come to India, each with their uniqu=\r\ne perspectives and ideas and philosophies. Each must individually try and f=\r\nind whose ideas gel properly with our mental and emotional makeup, and help=\r\n us to progress on the path. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Though I now have a very d=\r\neep respect for Sri Aurobindo, I maintain a safe distance from both his cri=\r\ntics and his blind-admirers. Both of them, in my opinion, have misunderstoo=\r\nd the depth of his teachings. Both their love and their hatred is a functio=\r\nn of their own egos, like it was mine 3 years ago, and not based on any gen=\r\nuine understanding or appreciation. In spirituality, no Sadguru can be unde=\r\nrstood accurately or even slightly without sincere sadhana.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;&lt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Disclaimer---- My thinking is &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ver=\r\ny different due to Darshan and=C3=82&nbsp;Grace of Divine Mother &amp; Divi=\r\nne &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Lord. Nobody should feel unhappy If I do not agree or follow t=\r\nhe &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; leader.Thanks.&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; I at-least will neve=\r\nr feel unhappy if you disagree. There are &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; many saints, many philo=\r\nsophies, many paths, not everyone is bound to &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; like every path.=C3=\r\n=82&nbsp; Disagreement is perfectly ok. Because someone &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; disagrees=\r\n with me or those whom I agree with, does not mean I like him &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; any=\r\n less. I try to keep my=C3=82&nbsp; emotional side (where respect, love, &lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; dislike, hatred, anger, passions exist) separate from my thinking m=\r\nind. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; It is very much possible, through practice, for a man to dis=\r\nassociate &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; his rational-mind from the emotional-mind. So have no f=\r\nears that your &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; disagreement is going to make me like you any less=\r\n or any more.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; The problem with the emotional part of our=\r\n being is that it jumps up at appearances, running ahead to grasp the truth=\r\n rather than waiting patiently for the truth to arrive in all its aspects a=\r\nnd dimensions, and in the process it distorts the truth and then reacts to =\r\nthat distorted image. For example, recently in some social forums I posted =\r\na comment that I found the Tantrik Adwaitha far more appealing than Sri Adi=\r\n Shankara&#39;s Adwaitha, though the Adwaitha of Adi Shankara has many hard-sel=\r\nling supporters. Immediately some friends of mine on Twitter and otherwise,=\r\n jumped to the false conclusion that I have disrespected Adi Shankara, and =\r\ntried best to make me &quot;see the truth&quot; by such grandiose statements that=C3=\r\n=82&nbsp; Shankara is the &#39;final word&#39; on Adwaitha and everything else must=\r\n be necessarily lesser. Or that I was making an egoistic denouncement. Both=\r\n of which are million light-years away from the truth. That Sri Adi Shankar=\r\na was a special Vibhuti&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  (manifestation) of God, that much I am ce=\r\nrtain. His compositions are so brilliant that it can&#39;t be sufficiently appr=\r\neciated in words. Yet, I have equally no qualms in rejecting his philosophy=\r\n. And because I am not bound to accept his philosophy, does not mean I resp=\r\nect or love him any less than any other great saint.=C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; If you disrespect a man, and specially a saint, and then start dis=\r\nliking him too with a passion, you are creating strong negative karmas. But=\r\n if you can disagree with someone without losing respect or love for the pe=\r\nrson, in an objective manner, you reap very little karmic effects. That is =\r\nwhy Lord Krishna too advices us to become more detached in life.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; In conclusion, Narasimha is totally correct. Many things cannot be=\r\n sufficiently expressed in words without causing some distortion.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; -Regards&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |&lt;br=\r\n&gt;\n&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; ________________________________&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  From: Laxmi Narayan &=\r\nlt;shrijishrihari@...&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; To: &quot;&lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mail=\r\nto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-w=\r\nisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;&quot; &lt;&lt;a rel=3D&quot;no=\r\nfollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;=\r\n href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@...=\r\nm&lt;/a&gt;&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Sent: Thursday, 11 October 2012 12:21 AM&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Subje=\r\nct: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: A thought&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&n=\r\nbsp; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Dear Rajarshi Bha=\r\ni,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; How are you doing? About 2